      "id": "171",
      "titolo": "Space geodesy and geodynamics: an overview",
      "timestamp": 1391526000,
      "descrizione": "The \"global change\", as well as various transient geophysical phenomena (e.g. earthquakes), significantly influence the Earth's global dynamics on different time scales. Thanks to space geodesy, it is possible to measure, with very high accuracy, time series of a number of global geodynamic parameters. The most important space geodetic observational techniques are Satellite\/Lunar Laser Ranging (SLR\/LLR), Very Long Baseline Interferometry (VLBI), Global Navigation Satellite Systems (GNSS), and spaceborne gravimetry\/gradiometry.\r\n\r\nWorldwide networks of such observatories are organized in \"services\" of the International Association of Geodesy (IAG), which contributes to the Global Earth Observation System of Systems (GEOSS) through the\r\nGlobal Geodetic Observing System (GGOS). This seminar will outline of the scientific framework, describe the main space geodetic observational techniques and methods, give an overview of the most\r\nrecent results, and highlight future prospects.",
